cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper deals with click-through-rate (CTR) estimation in sponsored search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses artificial neural networks (ANN) and decision trees, which are popular techniques in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), hence cs.CL is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves ML models and algorithms, which are relevant to cs.AI and cs.DS.
